      <table width="100%" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0" border="0" bordercolor="red">
        <tr>
          <td valign="top">

<span class="txth1">VimIRC.vim : An IRC client script</span> 

<br>
<br>

<!-- karma table -->
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="1" bordercolor="#000066">
<tr>
  <td class="lightbg"><b>&nbsp;script karma&nbsp;</b></td>
  <td>
    Rating <b>264/115</b>,
    Downloaded by 9576  </td>
  <td class="lightbg">
  <b>&nbsp;Comments, bugs, improvements&nbsp;</b>
  </td>
  <td>
    <a href="http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/Script:931">Vim wiki</a>
  </td>  
</tr>
</table>
<p>

<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
<tr><td class="prompt">created by</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=4697">Madoka Machitani</a></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">script type</td></tr>
<tr><td>utility</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">description</td></tr>
<tr><td>This is an IRC client which runs on Vim.&nbsp;&nbsp;It has some of the features<br>IRC users might expect, such as multiple servers connectivity, DCC<br>SEND/CHAT features etc..&nbsp;&nbsp;Read the plugin file for more feature info and<br>usage instructions.<br><br>For those who are unfamiliar with IRC in general, I recommend visiting<br>this site first: <a target="_blank" href="http://www.irchelp.org/">http://www.irchelp.org/</A><br><br>If you have any questions, problems, or suggestions etc., /query or<br>e-mail the maintainer.&nbsp;&nbsp;Do not direct them to the channel #vim please.<br><br>Screenshots:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a target="_blank" href="http://www.dd.iij4u.or.jp/~madokam/img/vimirc04.png">http://www.dd.iij4u.or.jp/~madokam/img/vimirc04.png</A><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a target="_blank" href="http://www.dd.iij4u.or.jp/~madokam/img/vimirc05.png">http://www.dd.iij4u.or.jp/~madokam/img/vimirc05.png</A> (invoking web browser)<br><br>Here is a minimum set of knowledge required to start/exit the script:<br><br>To start it, type<br><br>:VimIRC&lt;CR&gt;<br><br>Then you'll be prompted for some user info (nick, full name etc.).<br><br>Upon successfull connection, try some normal commands you're familiar<br>with (&quot;j&quot;, &quot;k&quot;, &quot;&lt;C-W&gt;-&quot;things and so on).&nbsp;&nbsp;Typing &quot;i&quot; or &quot;I&quot; will let<br>you in to the IRC-command mode, where you can enter commands such as<br>&quot;/join #vim&quot; and messages.<br><br>To quit, just press &quot;Q&quot;.<br><br>Another method of quitting: get out of the loop with &quot;&lt;C-C&gt;&quot;, then type<br><br>:VimIRCQuit&lt;CR&gt;<br><br>If you change your mind and want to get online again, press &quot;&lt;Space&gt;&quot; on<br>any of the VimIRC windows.<br><br>Have fun!</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">install details</td></tr>
<tr><td>Just drop the file into your plugin directory.<br><br>Requirements:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Vim 6.2 or later with perl interface enabled<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Perl 5.6 or later (5.8 or later if you want multibyte support)</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
</table>

