    <td class="roweven" valign="top" width="2000">A rather big change:<br>Single-window mode (g:vimirc_winmode == 'single') has become much useful.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each channel/server will now take its own window, and updates for hidden buffers will be done in the background.&nbsp;&nbsp;See the 2nd screenshot for an idea how it will work.<br><br>New commands:<br>1. SET: Use this command to set or show the values of internal options.&nbsp;&nbsp;Usage: &quot;/SET option value&quot;.&nbsp;&nbsp;Omit arguments to see the list of settable options.<br>2. &lt;C-N&gt; / &lt;C-P&gt; (Normal mode): Cycle through channels/servers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Useful in single-window mode.<br><br>A Fix: &quot;/JOIN 0&quot; was not working.</td>
